1.What is Python?What are the different ways to install in your PC?
A) Python is a general-purpose interpreted, interactive, object-oriented, and high-level programming language. It was created by Guido van Rossum during 1985- 1990.

Ways to install:

-->From the Python Software Foundation website at python.org
-->From the anaconda navigator.

2.What are code environments and types?
A) A code environment is a standalone and self-contained environment to run Python. Each code environment has its own set of packages.

Types:
*Text-Editors
* IDEs
* Notebook Environments
